We use two unordered sets to store words from both sentences. Then, we iterate through each word in one sentence and check if it is not present in the other sentence's set. If it is not present, we add it to the uncommon words vector. This approach has a time complexity of O(n) because we iterate through each word in one sentence and check against the other sentence. The space complexity is O(n) because we use two unordered sets and a vector to store the uncommon words.

